event.description: Have you tried every diet on the planet only to find yourself caving to the “forbidden” foods and giving up? Do you ever eat something even though you know you’re not physically hungry? If you had an easy way to naturally shrink the size of your stomach without surgery or even without dieting Would you be willing to abandon old habits and take control of your life?                                   Virtual Gastric Band—Mindful Eating                       For Health, Strength, Confidence, and Wellbeing 4 - Group Hypnosis Sessions designed to shrink your stomach and change eating habits 8-week Am I Hungry?® Mindful Eating Program with workbook 24 - Group Training Sessions 3/week for 8 weeks. Body fat measurements at the start and end of the program. Professional and group support for your success Virtual Gastric Band is a non-surgical and safe technique, which uses the power of hypnosis to retrain the mind to be satisfied with smaller portions.  It’s like ‘flicking a switch in the brain’.  It changes your attitude towards food and helps you take charge of your eating habits. This innovative technique was developed and lab tested in England (where Hypnosis is as mainstream as a doctor’s visit) with a 95% success rate. Having a foreign body inside your stomach (virtual or real) won’t deal with the emotional relationship with food.  Incorporating the Am I Hungry?® Mindful Eating Program adds an additional layer of understanding that allows you to take the emotion out of food so you can be in charge of your nutrition.  And Hypnosis back up solidifies the change in coping strategies for good. Karen Hand is a Board Certified Hypnotist and Hypnosis Instructor, NLP Master Practitioner, and EFT Facilitator. Karen owns Karen Hand Hypnosis, Chicago LLC   312-315-2100 Sharan Tash is a Certified Personal Trainer with special training in Women’s Fitness and an Am I Hungry?®Mindful Eating Facilitator.  Sharan owns TASH Fitness 847-379-5777. event.description: Looking for great jazz, R&B, funk and more in a fun, intimate setting? How about the Green Dolphin Lounge at – wait for it – the Central Area Senior Center. On the third Friday of the month, the center is transformed into a performance space, with noted local artists, good food and a no-host bar. Tickets are only $20 ($15 for Center Lifetime members) and are available online at http://centralareasrcenter.org/GreenDolphin.aspx or by calling 206-726-4926. The Central Area Senior Center is located at 500 30th Avenue. The summer 2016 lineup includes; Maurice Bailey of the Collective opening for Ayron Jones (July 15); Triple Treat Band at the Seafair Patio Party (August 7); and the great Josephine Howell (August 19). July 15 Ayron Jones, One of Seattle’s hottest up-and-comers with his Jimi Hendrix guitar style and Robert Cray Blues is electrifying. The great drummer Maurice Bailey of The Collective will open for a solo Ayron Jones. The Collective musical style is funky in the style of Frankie Beverly and Maze. The Collective is made up of local musician from the Seattle area including John Studamire a graduate from Garfield High School. He continues to hone his skills as one of the top Bassist in the Seattle area. August 7 Seafair Patio Party Triple Treat Band plays and sings it all, including R & B, funk, fusion, Top 40 and original music. Doors open for the party at 11:30 a.m. Enjoy the Blue Angels, hydroplane races and more! https://www.facebook.com/pages/Triple-Treat-Band/143905895646088 August 19 Josephine Howell’s gospel roots make you feel good as she sings from her heart and ignites your soul. She performs soul, jazz, rhythm and blues immersed in real life stories. She has performed in venues nationally and internationally, at the 2014 and 2015 Grammy Awards in Los Angeles with Macklemore and Ryan Lewis, with the song “Same Love.” https://www.facebook.com/josephine.howell1
event.title: Hot Summer Music Scene Lineup for 2016 at the Central Area Senior Center

event.description: Beginning Guitar Level 1 Classes Please note that the Level 1 classes are for absolute beginners, we start from scratch!  If you know a few chords and can change between them, please check out the level 2 class!  If you are not sure, email or call me! There are two Level 1 classes, one on Tuesdays and one on Wednesdays - they're the same class so pick the day/time that works best for your schedule. (FYI - the Tuesday class is usually less crowded, so if you can do Tuesdays please do!)   Tuesdays 6pm-7pmAugust 2nd - September 20orWednesdays 7:30pm-8:30pmAugust 3rd - September 21Playing guitar is fun as well as a great source of relaxation and self-discovery that can enhance your life on many levels. The group class environment is a fantastic way for you to learn as well as meet new people to play with. We encourage and inspire each other! You will learn and understand - • the parts of the guitar • how to tune the guitar • proper sitting position and how to hold the guitar • approx 8 chords over 8 weeks while learning 7 songs to practice them with • how to play “in time” and change between chords • help and guidance with singing and playing• a dynamic group experience (lots of cool people!) Each lesson is tailored to create a motivating atmosphere where you can experience your progress while learning to play the songs that you love! *Note: Satisfaction is Guaranteed.  If you're nervous about commiting to 8 weeks, you are welcome to try the first  class for the single class rate to see if the level feels like a good fit. For more information:  5-Star Rating on Yelp and  video testimonials! If you have any questions, please email Carrie or call her at 415-305-8494sfguitarlessons.com

event.description: 2016 ESSENCE MUSIC FESTIVAL New Orleans, LA  June 30 - July 3 , 2016 Past guests that register before Aug 1 will receive $50 off the total package price Essence Music Festival, known as "the party with a purpose", is an annual music festival which started in 1995 as a one-time event to celebrate the 25th anniversary of Essence, a magazine aimed primarily towards African American women. It is the largest event celebrating African-American culture and music in the United States. Locally referred to as Essence Fest, it has been held in New Orleans, Louisiana every year since 1995 except for 2006. It features artists simultaneously performing on a main stage as well as four standing room only superlounge stages. event.description: "Nobody doesn't like boogie woogie!" is Ezra Charles' jumping-off point, as he weaves a fascinating history of this bouncing, jiving piano format. Peppering the dialogue with his own stories of personal interaction with the Masters, he performs many of the most famous standards of this genre as he explains the relationship between Blues, Jazz, Ragtime and what was originally called "Texas-Style Piano." Accompanied by his son Jakob on percussion, they re-create the excitement of this favorite piano sound from a century ago. This will be a two-performance event, with shows on Saturday, Mar. 19, at 7:30 PM, and Sunday, Mar. 20, at 2:30 PM.
event.title: Ezra Charles presents "The Story of Boogie Woogie"

event.description: There are a lot of Savannah tours!  In 2002, smashing all of the barriers, the Sixth Sense Savannah Ghost Tour was the first ghost and paranormal stories tour to go above and beyond the usual Savannah sightseeing areas and tourism subject matter. The scary stories and haunted tales started in the Savannah historic district neighborhood where locals, family and friends chose to share their personal ghost stories exclusively with our  6th Sense World Company Founder. Covering paranormal and haunted story topics of poltergeist, hags, exorcism, missing cemeteries, disembodied spirit forms, and haunted hotels, this pioneering Savannah ghost tour is arguably our customer’s favorite and best known walking ghost tour in Savannah.  You may have read “Midnight in the Garden of Good and Evil”  a non-fiction murder mystery novel by John Berendt. We’ll bring those intriguing Savannah stories to life when you visit the Mercer House. How about the infamous Greek Revival haunted home at 432 Abercorn Street , one of Savannah’s most controversial and most haunted houses? If you’re just looking to whet your appetite with haunted stories, or want to dive full on in more paranormal activity, the Sixth Sense Savannah Ghost Tour has got you covered and will astonish with endearing to scary stories, start to finish! Voted one of TripAdvisor’s Top Activities in Savannah! The reviews speak volumes!  Among the favorite things to do in Savannah, once you too have settled on a ghost tour — no Savannah trip is complete without yet another — our fully-guided Bonaventure Cemetery Tours offered daily at 10 am & 2 pm.
event.title: Sixth Sense Savannah Ghost Tours

Gable Music Ventures is a Wilmington, Delaware event production and booking company behind World Cafe Live at the Queen's monthly Singer Songwriter Showcase, The Ladybug Festival, Rockabilly Rumble and Wilmo Rock Circus. Wilmo Wednesdays is a new partnership with World Cafe Live at the Queen and will serve as the primary platform where Gable finds artists for local and regional bookings. Every Wednesday starting at 7:00pm, Gable Music Ventures will present a curated variety show featuring live music of all genres, stand-up comedy, spoken word and slam poetry, story-telling and other forms of performance art. This is not an open mic; any interested performers need to contact Jeremy Hebbel in advance to register to perform by emailing. jeremy@gablemusicventures.com

In addition to the events listed above, Gable Music Ventures will also be actively looking for artists for the following opportunities: Cromwell's Tavern, Columbus Inn, Penn's Place, Extreme Pizza, Cool Spring Farmers Market, Co-Op Farmers Market and multiple events throughout the year in Smyrna, Delaware.

Follow Wilmo Wednesdays on Twitter - https://twitter.com/WilmoWednesdays and Gable Music Ventures on Facebook - https://www.facebook.com/GableMusicVentures to read about the lineups every Wednesday evening. These shows are free of charge and will be a wonderful way to discover new talent in the tri-state area.

event.description: Café 21's Gaslamp location has launched a new live music series 7-nights per week featuring varying genres of award-winning musicians, including: Rebecca Jade, Marcela Mendez, Camia Gonzalez and more. As guests enter, they will be greeted by live music in the bar area as the musicians light up the room in a refined-yet-casual vibe that Café 21 is known for. Café 21 hopes to honor the musical tradition of the previous tenant, Croce's, while giving San Diego an accessible venue for nightly live music accompanied by food and drinks. Guests can grab a seat at the bar for a drink or in the dining room for dinner and enjoy a different genre of music each night including: Rock 'n Roll, Pop, Opera, Flamenco, Classic Rock, and Country. The same musicians will be performing every week on their designated music genre night, including: Friday- Classic Hits: Camia Gonzalez- Singer/songwriter from Tijuana whose musical influence comes from listening to her mom sing the songs her father used to compose.
